<% content_for :title, "About - Clough for SC5" %>

<div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16 md:py-24">
  <div class="text-center mb-16">
    <p class="text-campaign-red font-semibold tracking-wider uppercase mb-4">About</p>
    <h1 class="font-display text-5xl md:text-6xl font-bold text-navy-900 mb-6">
      Meet Andrew Clough
    </h1>
  </div>

  <%# Bio Section %>
  <section class="mb-16">
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
      <div class="order-2 md:order-1">
        <div class="relative">
          <div class="w-full aspect-[4/5] bg-navy-200 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center">
            <span class="text-9xl">👤</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="order-1 md:order-2">
        <h2 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold text-navy-900 mb-6">
          A Conservative for District 5
        </h2>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-navy-700 leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            Andrew Clough is a lifelong conservative and proud resident of Rock Hill, South Carolina.
            Born and raised in the area, Andrew has deep roots in District 5 and understands the values
            and concerns of the people who call it home.
          </p>
          <p>
            After graduating from local schools, Andrew pursued a career that allowed him to serve his
            community while building the practical experience needed to be an effective representative.
            He knows what it means to work hard, pay taxes, and raise a family in South Carolina.
          </p>
          <p>
            As your State Representative, Andrew will bring common-sense leadership to Columbia. He'll
            fight for lower taxes, better education, and less government interference in your daily life.
            Andrew believes in limited government, fiscal responsibility, and putting South Carolina
            families first.
          </p>
          <p>
            When he's not working on the campaign, Andrew enjoys spending time with his family, attending
            local church, and being involved in community activities throughout District 5.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <%# Priorities Section %>
  <section class="mb-16">
    <div class="text-center mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold text-navy-900 mb-4">
        Andrew's Priorities
      </h2>
    </div>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <div class="bg-ivory-50 rounded-xl p-6">
        <div class="text-3xl mb-4">💰</div>
        <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-navy-900 mb-2">Fiscal Responsibility</h3>
        <p class="text-navy-600">
          Andrew will fight to lower taxes and reduce government spending. He believes your money
          belongs in your pocket, not in Columbia's bureaucracy.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-ivory-50 rounded-xl p-6">
        <div class="text-3xl mb-4">📚</div>
        <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-navy-900 mb-2">Education Excellence</h3>
        <p class="text-navy-600">
          Parents should have choices in their children's education. Andrew supports school choice
          and efforts to improve outcomes for all South Carolina students.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-ivory-50 rounded-xl p-6">
        <div class="text-3xl mb-4">🏛️</div>
        <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-navy-900 mb-2">Smaller Government</h3>
        <p class="text-navy-600">
          The government that governs least governs best. Andrew will work to reduce regulations
          and empower individuals and businesses to thrive.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-ivory-50 rounded-xl p-6">
        <div class="text-3xl mb-4">❤️</div>
        <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-navy-900 mb-2">Family & Community</h3>
        <p class="text-navy-600">
          Strong families make strong communities. Andrew will advocate for policies that support
          traditional family values and local community institutions.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <%# Values Section %>
  <section class="bg-navy-900 text-white rounded-2xl p-8 md:p-12">
    <div class="text-center mb-8">
      <h2 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Core Values</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
      <div class="text-center">
        <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-campaign-red rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-3xl mx-auto mb-4">🎯</div>
        <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Integrity</h3>
        <p class="text-ivory-300 text-sm">Andrew will always be honest with the people of District 5, even when the truth is hard to hear.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="text-center">
        <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-campaign-red rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-3xl mx-auto mb-4">💪</div>
        <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Courage</h3>
        <p class="text-ivory-300 text-sm">Andrew isn't afraid to stand up for conservative values, even when it's the tough thing to do.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="text-center">
        <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-campaign-red rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-3xl mx-auto mb-4">🤝</div>
        <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Service</h3>
        <p class="text-ivory-300 text-sm">Andrew believes in serving the people of District 5, not special interests or political parties.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>